	<!-- SCIENCE -->
	<section id="research" style="background:var(--dark); padding:20px 0 0 0;">
		<div class="sm-section">
			<div class="sm-eyebrow">Peer-Reviewed Research</div>
			<h2 class="sm-h2">The data <span>behind it.</span></h2>
			<p class="sm-section-sub" style="margin-bottom:0">Every zone threshold is grounded in published research. Not wellness trends. Not guesswork.</p>

			<div class="sm-sci-latest">
				<div class="sm-sci-latest-badge">Latest</div>
				<h3>Sauna Use & Dementia Risk</h3>
				<p>Men who used the sauna 4&ndash;7 times per week had a 77% lower risk of developing dementia and a 65% lower risk of Alzheimer's disease compared to those who used it once per week.</p>
				<div class="sm-sci-source">Laukkanen et al. &middot; Age and Ageing &middot; 2017</div>
			</div>

			<div class="sm-science-grid">
				<div class="sm-sci-card"><h3>Cardiovascular Protection</h3><p>Regular sauna use at sufficient core temperatures reduces risk of sudden cardiac death by up to 63% in the largest longitudinal study of its kind.</p><div class="sm-sci-source">Laukkanen et al. &middot; JAMA Internal Medicine &middot; 2018</div></div>
				<div class="sm-sci-card"><h3>Growth Hormone Surge</h3><p>Heat stress triggers a growth hormone surge of 2&ndash;5&times; baseline. The response is dose-dependent — more pronounced at higher core temperatures.</p><div class="sm-sci-source">Casanueva et al.</div></div>
				<div class="sm-sci-card"><h3>Heat Shock Proteins</h3><p>HSP70 and HSP90 activate when core temperature crosses &sim;38&deg;C. These molecular chaperones repair damaged proteins and reduce inflammation.</p><div class="sm-sci-source">Hussain et al. &middot; Journal of Applied Physiology &middot; 2019</div></div>
				<div class="sm-sci-card"><h3>BDNF — Brain Growth Factor</h3><p>Brain-derived neurotrophic factor rises significantly with heat exposure. Linked to improved mood, neuroplasticity, and cognitive protection.</p><div class="sm-sci-source">Rhonda Patrick &middot; FoundMyFitness</div></div>
				<div class="sm-sci-card"><h3>Cortisol Reduction</h3><p>Post-session cortisol drops significantly. Heat activates the parasympathetic nervous system — the same pathway triggered by meditation.</p><div class="sm-sci-source">Laukkanen et al. &middot; Kukkonen-Harjula et al.</div></div>
				<div class="sm-sci-card"><h3>Norepinephrine Spike</h3><p>Norepinephrine spikes up to 3&times; during heat exposure — sharpening focus and mood. The effect extends well beyond the session itself.</p><div class="sm-sci-source">Sr&aacute;mek et al. &middot; Journal of Applied Physiology &middot; 2000</div></div>
				<div class="sm-sci-card"><h3>All-Cause Mortality</h3><p>Frequent sauna users show a 40% lower risk of all-cause mortality. The benefit scales with frequency — more sessions, stronger the effect.</p><div class="sm-sci-source">Laukkanen et al. &middot; JAMA Internal Medicine &middot; 2018</div></div>
				<div class="sm-sci-card"><h3>Hypertension in Women</h3><p>Women who used the sauna regularly showed a 46% lower risk of developing high blood pressure — a significant finding for cardiovascular health across sexes.</p><div class="sm-sci-source">Zaccardi et al. &middot; American Journal of Hypertension &middot; 2017</div></div>
				<div class="sm-sci-card"><h3>Plasma Volume Expansion</h3><p>Repeated heat exposure increases plasma volume, improving oxygen delivery to muscles. This adaptation mirrors the effects of moderate aerobic training.</p><div class="sm-sci-source">Minson et al. &middot; American Journal of Physiology &middot; 2000</div></div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- PRICING -->
	<section id="pricing" style="background:var(--dark); border-top:1px solid rgba(232,93,4,0.12);">
		<div class="sm-section">
			<div class="sm-eyebrow">Pricing</div>
			<h2 class="sm-h2">Simple. <span>Everything included.</span></h2>
